cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories, as it presents a method for learning state representations in reinforcement learning. The paper also involves system and control (cs.SY) as it deals with state transition processes induced by a behavior policy. Additionally, the paper involves data structures (cs.DS) as it deals with the representation of graphs using the Laplacian matrix. Finally, the paper involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it uses a neural network to approximate the eigenvectors of the Laplacian.
